---
import { withBase } from '../../lib/url';
import Prose from '../../layouts/Prose.astro';
import Quote from '../../components/Quote.astro';
import QuoteList from '../../components/QuoteList.astro';
import { TECHNIQUES } from '../../lib/techniques';

const t = TECHNIQUES.find((x) => x.slug === 'judge-and-witnesses')!;
---

<Prose
  title={t.title}
  description={t.description}
  crumbs={[{ name: 'Techniques', href: '/techniques/' }, { name: t.title }]}
  kicker="Technique"
  jsonLd={[{ '@type': 'Article', headline: t.title }]}
>
  <p>
    At the foot of every shield chart stand three figures that sum up the whole. The
    <em>Right Witness</em> is made from the first and second Nieces, the <em>Left Witness</em> from
    the third and fourth, and the <em>Judge</em> from the two Witnesses together. The Witnesses show
    the parties, the beginning, and the course of the matter; the Judge gives its general summary,
    good or ill, before any house is examined.
  </p>

  <h2>Read the Judge and Witnesses</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Take the Right Witness, the Left Witness, and the Judge from the foot of the shield.</li>
    <li>Check that the Judge has an even number of points. An odd Judge means a miscast chart, so re-derive it before reading.</li>
    <li>Read the Right Witness for the querent's side and the start of the matter, and the Left Witness for the other side and its course.</li>
    <li>Read the Judge for the general outcome, good or ill.</li>
    <li>Look the two Witnesses up in Cattan's tables to find the answer for the matter in question.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>In the sources</h2>
  <p>
    Agrippa calls the Witnesses <em>Coadjutrices</em> or <em>Testes</em>, and the figure made from
    them the index of the whole figure:
  </p>
  <QuoteList topic="judge-witnesses" />
  <p>
    Crowley's <em>Handbook</em> preserves a complete set of tables (omitted from Regardie's
    Golden Dawn papers) giving the answer for every combination of Witnesses and Judge for ten
    standard matters (life, money, rank, property, marriage, children, sickness, prison, journeys
    and things lost): see <a href={withBase('/library/crowley/witnesses-and-judge/')}>the Tables of Witnesses
    and Judge</a> in the library.
  </p>
</Prose>
